com.asemantics.model
Interface CodeHandler

All Superinterfaces:
BackTrackingSupport, JavadocHandler, ParseHandler
All Known Implementing Classes:
CodeHandlerDebugImpl, CodeHandlerImpl, JStatistics.StatisticsCodeHandler
public interface CodeHandler
extends ParseHandler, JavadocHandler, BackTrackingSupport

This interface represents a code handler. An handler is domething able to receive code analysis events and use it to perform some analysis.

Author:
Michele Mostarda (michele.mostarda@gmail.com)

constructor

void constructor(JavaCodeModel.JModifier[] modifiers,
                 JavaCodeModel.JVisibility visibility,
                 int overloadIndex,
                 String[] parameterNames,
                 JavaCodeModel.JType[] parameterTypes,
                 JavaCodeModel.ExceptionType[] exceptions)
Notifies the parsing of a constructor. The length of paramterSize and parameterNames is the same, the association between these elements is done positionally.

Parameters:
modifiers - the constructor modifiers.
visibility - the visibility level for the constructor.
overloadIndex - the overload index for the constructor.
parameterNames - the array of parameter names.
parameterTypes - the array of parameter types.
exceptions - exceptions raised by the contructor.

            JavaCodeModel.JType returnType,
            JavaCodeModel.ExceptionType[] exceptions)
Notifies the parsing of a method. The method is expected to be FULLY QUALIFIED. The length of paramterSize and parameterNames is the same, the association between these elements is done positionally.

Parameters:
modifiers - the method modifiers.
visibility - the method visibility level.
pathToMethod - the fully qualified path to the method.
overloadIndex - the index of the current overload for the method.
parameterNames - the array of parameter names.
parameterTypes - the array of parameter types.
returnType - the return type of the method.
exceptions - exceptions raised by the method.
